                I graduated from Aquinas College in 2015 and moved on to studying Information Technology at Griffith University in 2016. Studying IT in high school was enjoyable, I grew a passion for it and wanted to continue learning it in University, 
                I was able to develop my employment skills from working at KFC and IGA. I developed customer service skills such as communicating with customers and resolving their issues. I worked at KFC on a casual basis during my final school year.
                I am currently employed at IGA on a casual basis in the grocery department making sure customers get what they want, have shelves filled and making sure we have stock for every product. 
                As a student embarking on the journey towards IT degree I am open to new experiences, that will allow me to develop my skills and my career.
                Please feel free to click on the links above to learn more about me and browse through my work. 
            </p>
